======================================================================
$ blade create file move -h
======================================================================
File move

Usage:
  blade create file move

Examples:

# Move the file /home/logs/nginx.log to /tmp
blade create file move --filepath /home/logs/nginx.log --target /tmp

# Force Move the file /home/logs/nginx.log to /temp
blade create file move --filepath /home/logs/nginx.log --target /tmp --force

# Move the file /home/logs/nginx.log to /temp/ and automatically create directories that don't exist
blade create file move --filepath /home/logs/nginx.log --target /temp --auto-create-dir


Flags:
      --auto-create-dir          automatically creates a directory that does not exist
      --blade-release string     Blade release package，use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --channel string           Select the channel for execution, and you can now select SSH
      --filepath string          file path (required)
      --force                    use --force flag overwrite target file
  -h, --help                     help for move
      --install-path string      install path default /opt/chaosblade，use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --override-blade-release   Override blade release，use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --ssh-host string          Use this flag when the channel is ssh
